\begin<<283>>tex2html_deferred<<283>>\par\end<<284>>tex2html_deferred<<284>>\question Consider a discrete-time input sequence \begin<<213>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<213>>$x[n]=\alpha^n u[n]$\end<<214>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<214>>\space fed to a system whose impulse response is \begin<<215>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<215>>$h[n] = u[n]$\end<<216>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<216>>\space defined for \begin<<217>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<217>>$n=0,1,2,3...$\end<<218>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<218>>. Compute the output sequence \begin<<219>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<219>>$y[n]$\end<<220>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<220>>\space generated by the system. (\begin<<221>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<221>>$0;SPMlt;\alpha;SPMlt;1$\end<<222>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<222>>) \textbf<<70>>(Hint: Discrete-time convolution)<<70>>
