\begin<<285>>tex2html_deferred<<285>>\par\end<<286>>tex2html_deferred<<286>>\question Consider a zero-mean periodic signal \begin<<231>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<231>>$f(t)$\end<<232>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<232>>\space with period \begin<<233>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<233>>$'T'$\end<<234>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<234>>\space such that it has the following property,
\begin<<83>>align*<<83>>
    f(-t) = -f(t)
\end<<84>>align*<<84>>
Suppose the fourier series expansion of such a signal is given by,
\begin<<85>>align*<<85>>
    f(t)=\sum_<<86>>n=1<<86>>^<<87>>\infty<<87>>a_n\cos\left(\frac<<88>>2\pi n<<88>><<89>>T<<89>>t\right)+\sum_<<90>>n=1<<90>>^<<91>>\infty<<91>>b_n\sin\left(\frac<<92>>2\pi n<<92>><<93>>T<<93>>t\right)
\end<<94>>align*<<94>>
Which of the following is true?
\begin<<95>>itemize<<95>>
    \item All the coefficients of even harmonics of both sine and cosine terms must always be zero.
    \item All the coefficients \begin<<235>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<235>>$b_n$\end<<236>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<236>>\space of the sine terms must be zero. 
    \item All the coefficients of odd harmonics of both sine and cosine terms must always be zero.
    \item All the coefficients \begin<<237>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<237>>$a_n$\end<<238>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<238>>\space of the cosine terms must be zero.
\end<<96>>itemize<<96>>
\question Suppose the output signal of a full wave rectifier is given by \begin<<239>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<239>>$f(t)$\end<<240>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<240>>, (Consider \begin<<241>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<241>>$f(t)$\end<<242>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<242>>\space to be a full-wave rectified sine wave with amplitude \begin<<243>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<243>>$'A'$\end<<244>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<244>>\space and \begin<<245>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<245>>$f(0)=0$\end<<246>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<246>>). The fourier series expansion of such a signal is given by,
\begin<<97>>align*<<97>>
    f(t)=a_0+\sum_<<98>>n=1<<98>>^<<99>>\infty<<99>>a_n\cos\left(\frac<<100>>2\pi n<<100>><<101>>T<<101>>t\right)+\sum_<<102>>n=1<<102>>^<<103>>\infty<<103>>b_n\sin\left(\frac<<104>>2\pi n<<104>><<105>>T<<105>>t\right)
\end<<106>>align*<<106>>
Which of the following is true?
\begin<<107>>itemize<<107>>
    \item \begin<<247>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<247>>$a_0$\end<<248>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<248>>\space is zero
    \item \begin<<249>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<249>>$a_0$\end<<250>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<250>>\space is non-zero and its value is given by \begin<<251>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<251>>$a_0=\frac<<108>>2A<<108>><<109>>\pi<<109>>$\end<<252>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<252>>
    \item \begin<<253>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<253>>$a_0$\end<<254>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<254>>\space is non-zero and its value is given by \begin<<255>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<255>>$a_0=\frac<<110>>A<<110>><<111>>2\pi<<111>>$\end<<256>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<256>>
    \item \begin<<257>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<257>>$a_n = 0$\end<<258>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<258>>, for all \begin<<259>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<259>>$n;SPMgt;0$\end<<260>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<260>>
\end<<112>>itemize<<112>>
